{
  "__fixture__": {
    "name": "partial_replay_provider_unavailable",
    "scenario": "A composer turn from an older release whose connected-provider model identity has since been retired by the vendor. The assembly, evidence packet, receipts, tainted-content fence, mutation lineage, and every context segment remain retained and unchanged. The provider availability record grades the originating provider / model as unreachable_retired; the current connected provider identity is still reachable but would route to a different identity. Replay grade resolves to partial_replay_provider_unavailable with degraded_capture_classes = [provider_identity, model_identity]. Every other capture class remains required_captured or required_captured_reference_only, preserving evidence honesty so a reviewer sees 'the provider is gone' rather than a silent best-effort reroute. The audit-storage manifest lists the retained artifacts with the unchanged record-class posture inherited from ai_retained_evidence_packet.",
    "exercised_contract_sections": [
      "replay_grade",
      "capture_class",
      "capture_posture",
      "provider_availability",
      "mutation_status",
      "storage_object_kind",
      "retention_posture_class",
      "export_posture_class"
